<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include('../partials/head') %>
        <title>Refund Policy - Paybilupi</title>
</head>

<body class="bg-mesh font-outfit d-flex flex-column min-vh-100">
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-white border-bottom border-light py-3">
        <div class="container">
            <a class="navbar-brand d-flex align-items-center gap-2" href="/">
                <div class="bg-primary bg-gradient text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center shadow-sm"
                    style="width: 36px; height: 36px;">
                    <i class="fi fi-rr-wallet fs-5 mt-1"></i>
                </div>
                <span class="fw-bold fs-4 tracking-tight text-main">Paybilupi</span>
            </a>
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
                <a href="/auth/login" class="btn btn-alt px-4 rounded-pill fw-semibold shadow-sm d-none d-sm-block">Sign
                    In</a>
                <a href="/auth/register" class="btn btn-premium px-4 rounded-pill fw-semibold shadow-sm">Get Started</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="container py-5 my-5 flex-grow-1">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-9">
                <div class="mb-5 border-bottom border-light pb-4" data-aos="fade-up">
                    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-main mb-3">Cancellation & Refund Policy</h1>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">Clear guidelines for subscriptions and consumer transactions.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="premium-card p-4 p-md-5" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
                    <div class="alert alert-primary bg-primary bg-opacity-10 border-0 mb-5 text-primary text-center">
                        <i class="fi fi-rr-info fs-4 d-block mb-2"></i>
                        <p class="mb-0 fw-semibold">Note: Paybilupi operates as a SaaS routing platform, not a bank. The
                            following policy governs payments made directly to Paybilupi for our software services, NOT
                            payments made between consumers and merchants utilizing our API links.</p>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">1. Refund Policy for SaaS Subscriptions</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-4">Paybilupi offers a completely free core tier. However, for merchants
                        upgrading to our Premium or Enterprise subscription plans (which may include features like
                        priority support or advanced routing configuration):</p>
                    <ul class="text-muted mb-5" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li><strong>14-Day Money-Back Guarantee:</strong> If you are unhappy with a premium subscription
                            within the first 14 days of upgrade, you may request a full, no-questions-asked refund by
                            generating a ticket in the Support dashboard.</li>
                        <li>Refunds requested after the 14-day window will be evaluated on a pro-rata basis at the sole
                            discretion of the Paybilupi billing department.</li>
                        <li>Payments for one-time setup fees or custom development (Enterprise SLA) are strictly
                            non-refundable once engineering work has commenced.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">2. Processing Consumer Refunds</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-4">Because Paybilupi routes your transactions directly into your connected
                        UPI/Wallet accounts (e.g., your personal / business PhonePe instance), the fiat money never
                        touches our corporate ledgers. Consequently:</p>
                    <ul class="text-muted mb-5" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li><strong>Paybilupi cannot initiate refunds to your customers on your behalf.</strong></li>
                        <li>If a consumer requests a refund for a product purchased from you via a Paybilupi link, you
                            (the Merchant) must log into your original gateway app (e.g., PhonePe Business) and manually
                            initiate the reversal to the customer.</li>
                        <li>We are currently developing API hooks to allow you to command reversals via the Paybilupi
                            dashboard, but ultimate execution remains dependent on the underlying gateway's policies.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">3. Chargebacks and Disputes</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-5">Merchants are entirely responsible for handling consumer chargebacks.
                        Since Paybilupi operates with 0% TDR and direct wallet settlement, chargeback disputes will be
                        raised by the consumer's bank directly against your connected wallet. Paybilupi will provide
                        transaction metadata logs to assist you in dispute resolution upon request, but assumes no
                        financial liability for lost chargeback arbitrations.</p>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">4. Requesting Cancellations</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">You may cancel your Paybilupi account and revoke our access to your
                        gateways at any time via the <span class="fw-bold text-main">Settings -> Profile -> Delete
                            Account</span> flow in the dashboard. Upon deletion, all subscription auto-renewals are
                        immediately halted.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>